---
title: Mario Batali's Spaghetti with Fresh Tomatoes, Chorizo, and Basil
description: Even the best recipes get even better when you're cooking for a good goal. Mario Batali's vibrant spaghetti dish was specially crafted for EAT (RED) SAVE LIVES. Featuring juicy, warm heirloom tomatoes, browned and crisped chorizo, and pasta cooked to a perfect al dente, it’s hearty, satisfying, and can be adjusted to match your ideal level of heat. As Mario says, Ain’t it delicious when good food does great things?
image: https://img.hellofresh.com/f_auto,fl_lossy,h_640,q_auto,w_1200/hellofresh_s3/image/mario-batalis-spaghetti-3285755e.jpg
pdf: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipecards/card/mario-batalis-spaghetti-d76091b9.pdf
author: Sara Heilman
cuisine: North America
nutrition:
  calories: 570 kcal
  fat: 24 g
  saturated fat: 7 g
  carbohydrates: 70 g
  sugar: 5 g
  protein: 22 g
  fiber: 4 g
  sodium: 300 mg
time required: 25 minutes
source: https://www.hellofresh.com/recipes/mario-batalis-spaghetti-58f935ebc9fd08410c7aa652
course: main course
servings: 2
---

Wash and dry all produce. Bring a large #pot of salted water to a boil. Thinly slice
@garlic{1/2%clove}(thinly sliced, use the rest as you like). Pick @basil{1/2%ounce} leaves
from stems. Roughly chop leaves and stems, keeping them separate. Thinly slice
@jalapeño{1%unit}(thinly sliced) until you have about 2 tsp, removing ribs and seeds for
less heat. Halve @heirloom grape tomatoes{4%ounce}(halved).

Once water is boiling, add @spaghetti{6%ounce} to #pot. Cook, stirring occasionally,
until al dente, about ~{9-11%minutes}. Reserve a few big splashes of pasta cooking
water, then drain.

While pasta cooks, heat @olive oil{1 1/2%tbsp} in a large #pan over medium heat. Add
garlic, basil stems, and @fresh pork chorizo{1/4%cup}(chopped, about 1/3 of the package),
breaking up meat into pieces. Cook, stirring, until chorizo is browned,
~{3-4%minutes}. Add jalapeño (to taste) and cook until fragrant, about
~{30%seconds}.

Add tomatoes to #pan. Cook until slightly softened, about ~{3%minutes}. Season with
@salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste}. Add drained spaghetti to #pan along with a splash
of pasta cooking water.

> TIP: Add just enough pasta cooking water to loosen things up—the starches will help
> everything adhere to the noodles and give the dish a beautiful consistency.

Toss everything in #pan until evenly combined and spaghetti is coated, about ~{1%minute}.
Remove from heat. Add basil leaves and @Parmesan cheese{1/4%cup}(grated, reserving a
little for garnish) and toss until well-combined and cheese has melted slightly.

Divide pasta between plates. Finish with a drizzle of @olive oil{3%tsp}, then garnish
with reserved basil leaves and Parmesan and serve.